			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="canskip">
			<shortinfo> Can you skip </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false (default) </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies whether sound effect playback can be skipped with a mouse click.<BR>
				　If true is specified, sound effect playback can be skipped by clicking the mouse.<BR>
				　However, please note that if the click skip is prohibited by the <ref tag="clickskip">clickskip</ref> tag, this skip cannot be performed.<BR>
				　Also, when skipped, the sound effect playback automatically stops.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Wait for the sound effect to finish playing.<BR>
		　If the sound effect is playing repeatedly, do not wait.
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="playvideo">
	<shortinfo> Play video / SWF </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>

	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
		<attrib name="storage">
			<shortinfo> file name </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> file name </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the name of the file to be played.<BR>
				　If you have already prepared for playback with <ref tag="openvideo">openvideo</ref> tags, you do not need to specify this attribute.<BR>
				　Conversely, if you do not use the openvideo tag, you must specify the file name here.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Play video or SWF (Shockwave Flash). Plays in the display area specified by the <ref tag="video">video</ref> tag. Since the video display area is hidden by default, it will not be displayed unless it is displayed with the video tag.<BR>
		　This tag does not wait for the video to finish playing. Use <ref tag="wv">wv</ref> to wait.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="openvideo">
	<shortinfo> Video / SWF playback preparation </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>

	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
		<attrib name="storage">
			<shortinfo> file name </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> file name </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the name of the file to be prepared for playback.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Prepare to play video or SWF (Shockwave Flash).<BR>
		　Generally, preparing to play a video takes time, so if you want to synchronize the playback timing with other things, you can use this tag to prepare only for playback first.<BR>
		　Use the <ref tag="playvideo">playvideo</ref> tag to play a ready-to-play video or SWF.<BR>
		　Even without using this tag, you can specify the file name to play with the playvideo tag and play it.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="position">
	<shortinfo> Message layer attributes </shortinfo>
	<group> Message operation </group>
	<attribs>

		<attrib name="layer">
			<shortinfo> Target layer </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> message0 or message1 or message </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the target message layer.<BR>
				　If omitted, the current message layer specified by the <ref tag="current">current</ref> tag will be selected.<BR>
				　If both this attribute and the page attribute are omitted, the current page and current message layer specified by the current tag are selected.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="page">
			<shortinfo> Target page </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "fore" or "back" </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the target page.<BR>
				　If you omit this attribute, the current page specified by the <ref tag="current">current</ref> tag will be selected.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="left">
			<shortinfo> Left end position </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Left end position (pixel unit) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the left edge position of the message layer.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="top">
			<shortinfo> Top position </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Top position (pixel unit) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the top position of the message layer.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="width">
			<shortinfo> width </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Width (pixel unit) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the width of the message layer.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="height">
			<shortinfo> height </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Height (pixel unit) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the height of the message layer.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="frame">
			<shortinfo> Frame picture </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> File name of frame image </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the image to be displayed as the frame image of the message layer. If not used, specify "". If "" is specified, the message layer will be displayed as a rectangle with the color and density specified by the color and opacity attributes.
				　The file with _m added to the file name (excluding extension) specified here will be read as the mask image, if any.
				Make sure to save the mask image in 256 color grayscale.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="framekey">
			<shortinfo> Color key for frame image </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0xRRGGBB format or palette index number or "adapt" </format>
			<info>
				　Specify which color of the frame image specified by the frame attribute is to be used as the extraction color. If omitted, the extraction color will be invalid. 
				　If you specify the extraction color in hexadecimal number in the format key=0xRRGGBB, the part painted with RR (red) GG (green) BB (blue) will be transparent as the extraction color.
				For example, key=0xff00ff specifies (r,g,b)=(255,0,255), which means that the true magenta part is to be made a transparent color and transparent.<BR>
				　If you simply specify a numerical value, the numerical value of that palette index will be the extraction color. Effective for 16-color / 256-color images.<BR>
				　If you specify key=adapt, the extraction color will be determined automatically.
				The color used is the color most used in the top line of the image.
				Effective for 16-color / 256-color images.<BR>
				　If you use a mask image, you do not need to specify this attribute.
			</info>
		</attrib>


		<attrib name="color">
			<shortinfo> Layer color </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0xRRGGBB format </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the display color of the message layer in 0xRRGGBB format. Effective when "" is specified for frame.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="opacity">
			<shortinfo> Layer opacity </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Opacity (0-255) </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies the opacity of the message layer as a number from 0 to 255 (not the opacity of the text or the opacity of the layer itself). 0 is completely transparent. Effective when "" is specified for frame.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="marginl">
			<shortinfo> Left margin </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Left margin (pixel unit) </format>
			<info>
				Specifies the left margin of the message layer.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="margint">
			<shortinfo> Top margin </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Top margin (pixel unit) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the top margin of the message layer.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="marginr">
			<shortinfo> Right margin </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Right margin (pixel unit) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the right margin of the message layer.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="marginb">
			<shortinfo> Bottom margin </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Bottom margin (pixel unit) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the bottom margin of the message layer.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="vertical">
			<shortinfo> Vertical writing mode </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "true" or "false" </format>
			<info>
				　Specify "true" to set the message layer to vertical writing mode.
				Specify "false" to write horizontally.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="draggable">
			<shortinfo> Can be dragged with mouse </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "true" or "false" </format>
			<info>
				　If set to true, the user can move the message layer by dragging with the mouse the area of the margin specified by marginl, margint, marginr, marginb and the opacity of the frame image is 64 or more.<BR>
				　If false is specified, this operation will not be performed.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="visible">
			<shortinfo> Visible </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "true" or "false" </format>
			<info>
				　If set to true, the message layer will be visible (displayed).<BR>
				　If set to false, the message layer will be invisible (hidden).
			</info>
		</attrib>


	</attribs>


	<remarks>
		　Specify various attributes for the message layer.<BR>
		　If you omit any attribute, the setting will not be changed.<BR>
		　Each attribute of marginl, margint, marginr, marginb is also used to specify the display area in the frame image specified by frame.
		　Can be set individually for the message layer (the back page / screen can be set differently).
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="quake">
	<shortinfo> Shake the screen </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="time">
			<shortinfo> Shaking period </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Number of characters or ms (milliseconds) </format>
			<info>
				　Shake the screen for as long as the number of characters specified here is displayed.<BR>
				　If ms is specified in the timemode attribute, it will be in milliseconds. If delay is specified, the shaking will continue for the character table speed specified by the <ref tag="delay">delay</ref> tag x the time specified in the time attribute of this tag.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="timemode">
			<shortinfo> Unit of time attribute </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "ms" or "delay" </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the unit of the time attribute.<BR>
				　The default of this setting follows defaultQuakeTimeInChUnit of Config.tjs.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="hmax">
			<shortinfo> Rolling maximum amplitude </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> pixel unit </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies the maximum lateral amplitude of the sway. If omitted, 10 is assumed.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="vmax">
			<shortinfo> Maximum pitch amplitude </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> pixel unit </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies the maximum vertical amplitude of the sway. If omitted, 10 is assumed.
			</info>
		</attrib>

	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Shake the screen.<BR>
		　This tag does not wait for the end of the shaking. Use the <ref tag="wq">wq</ref> tag to wait for the shaking to end.<BR>
		　Setting the vmax attribute to 0 results in rolling. Setting the hmax attribute to 0 results in pitching.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="cursor">
	<shortinfo> Change mouse cursor </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="default">
			<shortinfo> Normal mouse cursor </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Cursor constant starting with cr or cursor file name </format>
			<info>
				Specify a normal mouse cursor.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="pointed">
			<shortinfo> Mouse cursor when pointed </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Cursor constant starting with cr or cursor file name </format>
			<info>
				Specify the mouse cursor when pointing to a link or button.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="click">
			<shortinfo> Mouse cursor waiting for click </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Cursor constant starting with cr or cursor file name </format>
			<info>
				Specify the mouse cursor waiting for click.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="draggable">
			<shortinfo> Mouse cursor when dragging is possible </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Cursor constant starting with cr or cursor file name </format>
			<info>
				When draggable=true in the <ref tag="position">position</ref> tag, specify the mouse cursor that is displayed when the mouse comes to a position where the message layer can be dragged.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Change the mouse cursor. If you omit both attributes, the settings will not change.<BR>
		　For the mouse cursor constants starting with cr, please refer to "List of Mouse Cursor Constants" in the Kirikiri SDK Help. In that case, specify the constant with a &amp; symbol before the constant, such as <TT>default=&amp;crArrow</TT>.<BR>
		　A mouse cursor file with a .cur or .ani extension can be specified as the mouse cursor file (do not omit the extension).<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="loadplugin">
	<shortinfo> Loading plugins </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="module">
			<shortinfo> Plugin name </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Plugin file name </format>
			<info>
				Specify the plug-in file name you want to load.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Plugins loaded with this tag must be in one of the following:<BR>
		・Directly under the project folder<BR>
		・Plugin folder under the folder where the Kirikiri executable file is located<BR>
		・The folder containing the Kirikiri executable file<BR>
		<BR>
		　The extension of the plug-in specified by the module attribute cannot be omitted.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="mappfont">
	<shortinfo> Assigning rendered fonts </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="storage">
			<shortinfo> file name </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> file name </format>
			<info>
				Specifies the rendered font file that you want to assign to the current font.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Assigns the specified rendered font to the current font of the message layer currently being manipulated. After this tag, the specified rendered font will always be used when drawing the font in Kirikiri.<BR>
		　The font to be assigned does not need to actually exist. For example, you can use mappfont with the font "Hogehoge Font" selected to assign any rendered font to that "Hogehoge Font". You can only assign one rendered font to a font name (for example, you can't assign multiple differently rendered fonts to a font name).<BR>
		　You can also assign multiple rendered fonts to different fonts.
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="stopquake">
	<shortinfo> Stop shaking the screen </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
	<remarks>
		　End the shaking that started with the <ref tag="quake">quake</ref> tag.<BR>
		　The shaking can be ended without waiting for the number of times specified by the time attribute of the quake tag.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="r">
	<shortinfo> Begin on a new line </shortinfo>
	<group> Message operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="eol">
			<shortinfo> Whether it is a line feed at the end of the line </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true </format>
			<info>
				If ignoreCR of Config.tjs is false, KAG will generate an r tag at the time of a line break. This attribute does not exist for the [r] tag written in the scenario.<BR>
				This attribute is used when you want to distinguish between line break and [r] tag inside TJS script, so there is no meaning to specify this attribute in KAG scenario.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>
	<remarks>
		　Start a new line.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="ch">
	<shortinfo> Display characters </shortinfo>
	<group> Message operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="text">
			<shortinfo> Character to display </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> letter </format>
			<info>
				　The character specified here is displayed.<BR>
				　You can specify more than one character, but there is no automatic line break (the message history layer will not break if you specify more than one character here). Also, if multiple characters are specified, they are displayed at once (much faster than nowait). Usually only one character is specified.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>
	<remarks>
		　Displays characters in the message layer specified by the current tag. Not usually used.<BR>
		　Inside KAG, ordinary characters are processed by decomposing all characters one by one into this tag.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="hch">
	<shortinfo> Show vertical, medium, and horizontal </shortinfo>
	<group> Message operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="text">
			<shortinfo> Character to display </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> letter </format>
			<info>
				　The characters specified here are displayed horizontally only.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
		<attrib name="expand">
			<shortinfo> Whether to expand line spacing </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false (default) </format>
			<info>
				　If true, automatically expands line spacing when you try to draw a long vertical, medium, or horizontal color. If false, the vertical, middle and horizontal sides may not be drawn correctly, but the line spacing remains intact (usually false for two-digit characters).<BR>
				If this attribute is not specified, it is assumed to be false.<BR>
				<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>
	<remarks>
		　Displays characters in vertical, medium and horizontal (a way of writing horizontally only there when writing two digits in vertical writing).<BR>
		　The current message layer must be in vertical mode.<BR>
	</remarks>
	<example>
		今日は平成[hch text="15"]年[hch text="12"]月[hch text="30"]日
	</example>
</tag>

<tag name="resetfont">
	<shortinfo> Restore character attributes to default </shortinfo>
	<group> Message operation </group>
	<remarks>
		　Returns the attribute of the character specified by the <ref tag="font">font</ref> tag to the default.<BR>
		　Character attributes can be set individually for each message layer.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="ruby">
	<shortinfo> Ruby specification </shortinfo>
	<group> Message operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="text">
			<shortinfo> ruby </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Characters displayed as ruby </format>
			<info>
				Specify the characters to be displayed as ruby.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Specify ruby for the next character.<BR>
		　If you want to display ruby, please specify each time.<BR>
		　If you want to add ruby to multiple characters, you need to specify ruby for each character.<BR>
	</remarks>
	<example>
		　[ruby text="かん"]漢[ruby text="じ"]字
	</example>
</tag>

<tag name="edit">
	<shortinfo> Creating a single-line edit </shortinfo>
	<group> Form operations </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="name">
			<shortinfo> Variable name </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Variable name </format>
			<info>
				　Specify a variable to store the input character string.<BR>
				　If the variable already contains a string, it will be displayed as the initial string for single-line editing.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="length">
			<shortinfo> width </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Width (pixel unit) </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies the width (height for vertical writing) of the single line edit in pixels.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="bgcolor">
			<shortinfo> Background color </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0xRRGGBB format </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the background color in 0xRRGGBB format.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="opacity">
			<shortinfo> Background color opacity </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0 (completely transparent) to 255 (completely opaque) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the opacity of the background color specified by the bgcolor attribute from 0 to 255.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="color">
			<shortinfo> Letter color </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0xRRGGBB format </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the font color in 0xRRGGBB format.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="maxchars">
			<shortinfo> Maximum number of characters </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Maximum number of characters </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the maximum number of characters that can be entered. Specify 0 for unlimited.<BR>
				　Default is unlimited.
			</info>
		</attrib>

	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Creates an input field (edit) at the current position of the message layer that is the current operation target, in which the character string of only one line can be edited with the current font.
		　The edited string will not be assigned to the specified variable until the <ref tag="commit">commit</ref> tag is executed.
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="checkbox">
	<shortinfo> Creating a check box </shortinfo>
	<group> Form operations </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="name">
			<shortinfo> Variable name </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Variable name </format>
			<info>
				　Specify a variable to store the state of the check box.<BR>
				　If the variable is 0 (or undefined) it is considered unchecked, otherwise it is considered checked.<BR>
				　If the variable is already non-zero, the checkbox will be created with the checkbox checked.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="bgcolor">
			<shortinfo> Background color </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0xRRGGBB format </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the background color in 0xRRGGBB format.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="opacity">
			<shortinfo> Background color opacity </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0 (completely transparent) to 255 (completely opaque) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the opacity of the background color specified by the bgcolor attribute from 0 to 255.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="color">
			<shortinfo> Check mark color </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0xRRGGBB format </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies the color of the check mark in 0xRRGGBB format.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Creates a check box at the current position of the message layer currently being operated on.<BR>
		　The checkbox state is not assigned to the specified variable until the <ref tag="commit">commit</ref> tag is executed.<BR>
		　When the commit tag is executed, the variable will contain 1 if the check box is checked and 0 if it is not.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="commit">
	<shortinfo> Confirmation of form contents </shortinfo>
	<group> Form operations </group>

	<remarks>
		　Confirms the contents of "form elements" such as all edits and check boxes on the message layer that is currently operated.<BR>
		　When the content is finalized, the string or status that was edited in the form element is actually assigned to each variable.<BR>
		　Each form element will be deleted with a tag that deletes the message layer such as <ref tag="er">er</ref> or <ref tag="ct">ct</ref> tag, so you need to execute the commit tag before that.
	</remarks>

	<example>
		*editname<BR>
		@er<BR>
		Last name: [edit name="f.sname" length=200][r]<BR>
		First name: [edit name="f.name" length=200][r]<BR>
		[link target=*ok]OK[endlink][r]<BR>
		[link target=*cancel]Cancel[endlink][s]<BR>
		*ok<BR>
		; OK selected<BR>
		; Perform commit and assign to variables<BR>
		[commit]<BR>
		[jump target=*exit]<BR>
		*cancel<BR>
		; Cancel selected<BR>
		; Do not commit<BR>
		[jump target=*exit]<BR>
	</example>

</tag>




<tag name="s">
	<shortinfo> Stop </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
	<remarks>
		　Stop execution of the scenario file.<BR>
		　Write this tag when waiting for a choice with the <ref tag="link">link</ref> tag.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="stopvideo">
	<shortinfo> Stop video / SWF playback </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>

	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>


	<remarks>
		　Stop playing video / SWF.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="tempsave">
	<shortinfo> Saving bookmarks on memory </shortinfo>
	<group> Bookmark / pass record operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="place">
			<shortinfo> Storage location </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0 or a positive integer (0 is the default) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the bookmark number.If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				　There is no limit on the number that can be specified and the number of storage locations, but do not specify a very large integer.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　The information at the current position is inserted between the "bookmarks" on the memory. It is not a file but a bookmark in memory that is saved here, so the contents are not retained even after KAG ends, and have nothing to do with a normal bookmark.<BR>
		　Also, instead of saving the state at the label position that passed last, the information at the position where this tag is located is recorded. Also, the contents of the variables are not recorded.<BR>
		　Use in combination with <ref tag="tempload">tempload</ref> tags.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="tempload">
	<shortinfo> Reading bookmarks from memory </shortinfo>
	<group> Bookmark / pass record operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="place">
			<shortinfo> Storage location </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0 or a positive integer (0 is the default) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the bookmark number.If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="se">
			<shortinfo> Whether to load sound effects </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true (default) or false </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies whether to import sound effect information when importing.<BR>
				　If false is specified, the sound effect information will not be read (the current sound effect will continue to sound).
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="bgm">
			<shortinfo> Load background music </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true (default) or false </format>
			<info>
				　Specify whether to import background music information when importing.<BR>
				　If false is specified, BGM information will not be read (the current BGM will continue to be played).
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="backlay">
			<shortinfo> Whether to load front page to back page </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false (default) </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies whether to read the foreground layer information without loading the foreground layer information when loading, and to load the foreground layer information into the background layer.<BR>
				　If true is specified, the information recorded as the front page in the "bookmark" on the memory is actually read to the back page, and the front page remains as it is.
			</info>
		</attrib>
		
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Read the "bookmark" on the memory saved with the <ref tag="tempsave">tempsave</ref> tag.<BR>
		　However, the difference from normal reading of bookmarks is that execution does not move to the saved position, execution continues as it is, and the contents of variables do not change.<BR>
		　The message layer is not deleted. In addition, the behavior at the time of loading can be controlled by the se, bgm, and backlay attributes.<BR>
		　The main use case is to save the state once with the tempsave tag before entering the demo scene, etc., and return with this tag when the demo scene is over. Use this to quickly restore the settings.<BR>
		　It can also be used to temporarily save information in the right-click subroutine specified by rclick.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="hidemessage">
	<shortinfo> Dismiss message </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>

	<remarks>
		　Hide the message layer temporarily. Performs the same operation as selecting "Clear message" from the menu.<BR>
		　After waiting for the click, the message layer is displayed and execution continues.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="record">
	<shortinfo> Make a passage record </shortinfo>
	<group> Bookmark / pass record operation </group>

	<remarks>
		　Record the passage at the current position.<BR>
		　In the pass record, the position of the "label that can save a bookmark" immediately before is recorded, and when returning, it returns to that position, but the timing when it is actually recorded as a pass record is It is when I passed the "label that can save bookmarks".<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>



<tag name="showhistory">
	<shortinfo> View message history </shortinfo>
	<group> Message history operation </group>

	<remarks>
		　Displays the message history.<BR>
		　Execution continues when message history display ends.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="hact">
	<shortinfo> Message history action </shortinfo>
	<group> Message history operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="exp">
			<shortinfo> Expression to execute </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> TJS expression </format>
			<info>
				　Specify a TJS expression to execute when you click the message.
			</info>
		</attrib>

	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Specify the action for the message history. The part between this tag and the <ref tag="endhact">endhact</ref> tag can be clicked on the message history, and you can specify the TJS expression to be executed when clicked. It can be used to play voices that have been played back together with messages in the past by clicking on the message history.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="endhact">
	<shortinfo> End message history action </shortinfo>
	<group> Message history operation </group>

	<remarks>
		Ends the message history action set by the <ref tag="hact">hact</ref> tag (clears the settings).
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="rclick">
	<shortinfo> Right-click settings </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>

	<attribs>
		<attrib name="call">
			<shortinfo> Call a subroutine </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false </format>
			<info>
				　If set to true, right click will call the subroutine specified by storage and target attributes. Specifying false for both the jump attribute and this attribute will result in the normal "clear message" behavior.<BR>
				　This attribute and the jump attribute cannot be set to true at the same time.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="jump">
			<shortinfo> Jump to specified location </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false </format>
			<info>
				　If set to true, right click will jump to the location specified by the storage and target attributes. If you specify false for both the call attribute and this attribute, the normal "delete message" behavior occurs.<BR>
				　This attribute and call attribute cannot be set to true at the same time.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="target">
			<shortinfo> Subroutine call / jump destination </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> label </format>
			<info>
				　If the call attribute or the jump attribute is set to true, specify the label of the call destination / jump destination.<BR>
				　If this attribute is set to target="", execution will start from the beginning of the file specified by the storage attribute.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="storage">
			<shortinfo> Subroutine call destination / jump destination file </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> File </format>
			<info>
				　If the call attribute or the jump attribute is set to true, specify the call destination / jump destination file.<BR>
				　When this attribute is set to storage="", the label in the file at the time of right-clicking is searched.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="enabled">
			<shortinfo> Right click action </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false </format>
			<info>
				　If set to true, right-click hides the message layer, calls a specified routine, or jumps to a specified location.<BR>
				　If false is specified, these actions are not performed.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="name">
			<shortinfo> Menu item name </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Menu item name or "default" </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the menu item name of "clear message" in the system menu.<BR>
				　If name=default, it will default to "delete message".<BR>
				　To specify a menu hotkey (underlined letter in a menu item), use &amp; followed by a letter (for example, "Delete message (&amp;S)").
			</info>
		</attrib>

	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Set the operation when right-clicking or pressing the ESC key from the keyboard.<BR>
		　If you omit any attribute, the setting will not be changed.<BR>
		　These features can only be activated when waiting for clicks on [l] and [p] tags and when stopping on [s] tags.
	</remarks>

	<example>
	@rclick call=true target="*rclick" name="Call right click subroutine (&amp;S)" enabled=true<BR>
	<BR>
	*rclick<BR>
	@rclick jump=true target="*exit" name="Return (&amp;S)" enabled=true<BR>
	@current layer=message1<BR>
	@layopt layer=message1 page=fore visible=true<BR>
	@er<BR>
	This is inside the right click routine.<BR>
	@s<BR>
	*exit<BR>
	@layopt layer=message1 page=fore visible=false<BR>
	@current layer=message0<BR>
	@rclick call=true target="*rclick" name="Call right click subroutine (&amp;S)" enabled=true<BR>
	@return<BR>
	</example>
</tag>




<tag name="save">
	<shortinfo> Save bookmarks </shortinfo>
	<group> Bookmark / pass record operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="place">
			<shortinfo> Storage location </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0 or a positive integer (0 is the default) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the bookmark number.If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				　You can specify any number, but 999-1999 are bookmarks with special meaning.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="ask">
			<shortinfo> To confirm </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false (default) </format>
			<info>
				　If true is specified, confirm whether to save bookmarks. If false is specified, there is no confirmation whether to save the bookmark. If this attribute is omitted, it is assumed that false is specified.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Saves to the specified bookmark in non-free save mode. Performs the same operation as selecting "Hold a bookmark" from the menu.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="load">
	<shortinfo> Loading bookmarks </shortinfo>
	<group> Bookmark / pass record operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="place">
			<shortinfo> Storage location </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0 or a positive integer (0 is the default) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the bookmark number.If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				　You can specify any number, but 999-1999 are bookmarks with special meaning.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="ask">
			<shortinfo> To confirm </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false (default) </format>
			<info>
				　If true is specified, check whether to follow the bookmark. If false is specified, there is no confirmation whether to follow the bookmark. If this attribute is omitted, it is assumed that false is specified.<BR>
				　If the user selects "No" in the confirmation following the bookmark, execution will continue as it is.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　In non-free save mode, read from bookmarks. This is the same operation as selecting "Follow Bookmark" from the menu.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="erasebookmark">
	<shortinfo> Clear bookmarks </shortinfo>
	<group> Bookmark / pass record operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="place">
			<shortinfo> Bookmark number to delete </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0 or a positive integer (0 is the default) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the bookmark number.If omitted, 0 is assumed.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Deletes the bookmark with the specified number in non-free save mode. Bookmark becomes "(not set)".
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="copybookmark">
	<shortinfo> A copy of the bookmark </shortinfo>
	<group> Bookmark / pass record operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="from">
			<shortinfo> Bookmark number of copy source </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> 0 or a positive integer </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the bookmark number of the copy source.If omitted, 0 is assumed.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="to">
			<shortinfo> Bookmark number of copy destination </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> 0 or a positive integer </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the number of the bookmark to copy to.If omitted, 0 is assumed.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　In non-free save mode, the contents are copied from the bookmark specified by the from attribute to the bookmark specified by the to attribute.
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="disablestore">
	<shortinfo> Temporarily disable the bookmarker function </shortinfo>
	<group> Bookmark / pass record operation </group>

	<attribs>
		<attrib name="store">
			<shortinfo> The function of "insert bookmark" </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true (default) or false </format>
			<info>
				　Specify whether to disable the "insert bookmark" function.<BR>
				　Set to true to disable.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="restore">
			<shortinfo> "Follow the bookmark" function </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false (default) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify whether to disable the "follow bookmarker" function.<BR>
				　Set to true to disable.<BR>
				　Unlike the store attribute, this is assumed to be false if the attribute is omitted.
			</info>
		</attrib>

	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Temporarily disable the function of "insert bookmark".<BR>
		　After that, the function of "inserting a bookmark" will be unavailable unless you pass through a saveable label.<BR>
		　Immediately after KAG startup, this "Unavailable" and "Shiori Shiori" are disabled and you cannot use the "Shiori Shiori" function unless you pass a saveable label.<BR>
		　Write it in a place where there is no choice but to place a bookmark, such as the main menu of the game.<BR>
		　In contrast to this tag, the <ref tag="store">store</ref> tag allows you to permanently disable or enable both the bookmarking and tracking functions.
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="store">
	<shortinfo> Bookmark function setting </shortinfo>
	<group> Bookmark / pass record operation </group>

	<attribs>
		<attrib name="enabled">
			<shortinfo> Enable / Disable setting </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> true or false </format>
			<info>
				　Specify true to enable the bookmarker function, false to disable it. If false is specified, save / load by bookmark will not be possible.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Specify whether to enable or disable the bookmark function. Use <TT>[store enabled=false]</TT> if you do not want the user to perform save / load operations. <BR>
		　Unlike the <ref tag="disablestore">disablestore</ref> function, the store tag sets both the bookmarking and tracing functions permanently, whereas the disablestore tag sets the bookmark only for a short period of time before passing the saveable label. Just deactivate the "insert bookmark" or "follow" function. For convenience, disablestore is better.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="history">
	<shortinfo> Message history settings </shortinfo>
	<group> Message history operation </group>

	<attribs>
		<attrib name="output">
			<shortinfo> Output of character information </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false </format>
			<info>
				　Specify whether to output character information to the message history.<BR>
				　If true is specified, the characters displayed in the message layer will be displayed in the message history.<BR>
				　The first time you run the scenario, it is true.<BR>
				　If false is specified, no character information is output to the message history.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="enabled">
			<shortinfo> Can display message history </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies whether the message history can be displayed.<BR>
				　If true is specified, display is possible, if false is specified, display is disabled.<BR>
				　Set to false if you don't want users to see the message history.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
	　Make settings related to the message history function.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="hr">
	<shortinfo> Line break / Page break in message history </shortinfo>
	<group> Message history operation </group>

	<attribs>
		<attrib name="repage">
			<shortinfo> Page break </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false (default) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify whether to perform a page break.<BR>
				　If true is specified, a page break is performed instead of a line break. If false is specified, a line break is performed.<BR>
				　If this attribute is omitted, false is assumed.<BR>
				　Page break does not work unless everypage is set to true in the message history setting of Config.tjs.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
	　Line break or page break in message history.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="clickskip">
	<shortinfo> Click skip setting </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="enabled">
			<shortinfo> Enable / Disable setting </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> true or false </format>
			<info>
				　Specify true to enable the click skip function, false to disable it.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Click skip is a function that interrupts transitions and automatic movements by clicking the screen while displaying a message, or displays sentences at a stretch until you click.<BR>
		　You may want to disable it in demo scenes.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="nextskip">
	<shortinfo> Setting "Go to next choice" </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="enabled">
			<shortinfo> Enable / Disable setting </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> true or false </format>
			<info>
				　Specify true to enable the "Proceed to next choice" function, false to disable it.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>
	
	<remarks>
		　You can specify whether users can use the "Go to Next Choice" feature.<BR>
		　You may want to disable it in demo scenes.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="cancelskip">
	<shortinfo> Cancel skip </shortinfo>
	<group> Message operation </group>
	<remarks>
		　Cancel the skip state.<BR>
		　The skip state is a state in which click skip (a function that displays a sentence at a stretch until the user clicks the screen while clicking a message while displaying a message) and a state in which skipping is performed with "the next option is completed".<BR>
		　This does not mean that the "go to next choice" feature is disabled or that the click-skip feature itself is disabled thereafter.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="cancelautomode">
	<shortinfo> Cancel "Read automatically" </shortinfo>
	<group> Message operation </group>
	<remarks>
		　Forcibly cancel "Read automatically".<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="waittrig">
	<shortinfo> Wait for trigger </shortinfo>
	<group> Variable / TJS operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="name">
			<shortinfo> Trigger name </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Trigger name </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the trigger name to wait.
				　By specifying the same trigger name as an argument in the trigger method of the kag object (MainWindow class), the trigger can be activated and the waiting state can be released.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
		<attrib name="canskip">
			<shortinfo> Can you skip </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false (default) </format>
			<info>
				　If you specify true, you can skip the waiting action by clicking.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
		<attrib name="onskip">
			<shortinfo> When skipped </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> TJS expression </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the TJS expression to execute when skipped by clicking.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Wait for the TJS2 script to call the trigger method.<BR>
		　A "trigger" is a mechanism used to temporarily stop the progress of a scenario and wait for some processing in a KAG that operates in an event-driven programming model.<BR>
		　Use this tag to wait for the TJS2 script to finish processing.<BR>
		　For example, the trigger name "click" is a trigger that fires when the mouse is clicked (this is a trigger already defined inside KAG). You can wait for a mouse click by writing [waittrig name="click"].<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="clearvar">
	<shortinfo> Clear all game variables </shortinfo>
	<group> Variable / TJS operation </group>
	<remarks>
		　Clear all game variables. All game variables are undefined.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="clearsysvar">
	<shortinfo> Clear all system variables </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
	<remarks>
		　Clear all system variables.
	</remarks>
</tag>



<tag name="input">
	<shortinfo> String input </shortinfo>
	<group> Variable / TJS operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="name">
			<shortinfo> Variable name </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Variable name </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the variable that stores the character string you want to enter.<BR>
				　If the variable already contains a string, that string will be displayed as the initial string in the dialog box.<BR>
				　The variable does not change when the user presses the Cancel button or ESC key in the dialog box.<BR>
				　Variables can be any variables accessible from KAG.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="prompt">
			<shortinfo> prompt </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> The string to display as the prompt </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies the dialog box prompt (the character string displayed immediately above the input field). If omitted, it will be blank.<BR>
				　For example, "Please enter your name."
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="title">
			<shortinfo> title </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Dialog box title </format>
			<info>
				　Specify a title for the dialog box.<BR>
				　If omitted, the title will be blank.<BR>
				　For example, "Enter name".
			</info>
		</attrib>

	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Opens a dialog box to enter a string and prompts the user for input.<BR>
		　You can use it to enter a user name.<BR>
	</remarks>

	<example>
		[eval exp="f.username='Taro'"]<BR>
		[input name=f.username prompt="Please enter your name" title="Enter name"]<BR>
		Name is: [emb exp=f.username]<BR>
	</example>

</tag>


<tag name="title">
	<shortinfo> Title specification </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>

	<attribs>
		<attrib name="name">
			<shortinfo> title </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> title </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the title you want to display.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Specify the characters to be displayed on the task bar and window caption (title bar).<BR>
		　Usually the title of the game.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="video">
	<shortinfo> Specify attributes of video / SWF display area </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="visible">
			<shortinfo> Visible / invisible </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies whether to show the video / SWF display area (if true) or not (if false).
				Video / SWF can be played even when hidden (not displayed).<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="left">
			<shortinfo> Left end position </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Left end position (pixel unit) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the left edge of the display area.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="top">
			<shortinfo> Top position </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Top position (pixel unit) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the top position of the display area.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="width">
			<shortinfo> width </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Width (pixel unit) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the width of the display area. In the current version, the specification is ignored in the layer drawing mode.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="height">
			<shortinfo> height </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Height (pixel unit) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the height of the display area. In the current version, the specification is ignored in the layer drawing mode.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="loop">
			<shortinfo> Whether to loop </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false </format>
			<info>
				　Specify true if you want to loop.
			</info>
		</attrib>


		<attrib name="position">
			<shortinfo> Destination time </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Time (ms) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify this when you want to move the video playback position to the specified time.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="frame">
			<shortinfo> Destination frame </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Frame number </format>
			<info>
				　Specify this to move the video playback position to the specified position.<BR>
				　Unlike the position attribute, this attribute can be specified in frame units.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="mode">
			<shortinfo> Drawing mode </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "overlay" or "layer" </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the drawing mode of the movie.<BR>
				　Specify "overlay" to play in overlay mode. In overlay mode, the video cannot be deeper than other layers, but it can reduce the playback load.<BR>
				　Specify "layer" to play in layer drawing mode. In layer drawing mode, the video image can be displayed on the layer, but the playback cost is higher than "overlay". The layers to be displayed are set with <ref tag="videolayer">videolayer</ref> tags.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="playrate">
			<shortinfo> Playback speed </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Playback speed (value greater than 0.0) </format>
			<info>
				　Set the media playback speed.<BR>
				　Possible values are determined by the DirectShow filter.<BR>
				　NOTE: For MPEG files with audio, values between 0.0 and 2.0 can be set. In the case of MPEG files without audio, it can be set within the range of double (probably) from a value greater than 0.0, but the actual playback speed is limited by the processing speed.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="volume">
			<shortinfo> Volume </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Volume% (0-100) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the volume in %.
				　100 is the upper limit. Only volume control is supported (amplification is not possible due to the characteristics of the sound source).
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="pan">
			<shortinfo> Pan </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Bread (-100~0~100) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the pan (left and right sound image positions).<BR>
				　-100 is perfect left, 0 is center, and 100 is perfect right.<BR>
				　The middle value is 0, which means both channels are at full volume.<BR>
				　 If one channel is attenuated, the other will remain at full volume.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="audiostreamnum">
			<shortinfo> Audio stream number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Audio stream number (0-) </format>
			<info>
				　Enables the specified audio stream number.
			</info>
		</attrib>

	</attribs>

	<remarks>
	　Specify the attributes of the video / SWF display area.<BR>
	　The video / SWF display area is hidden by default, so it will not be displayed unless it is displayed with this tag.<BR>
	　The area displayed in overlay mode is not a layer. Appears before all layers.<BR>
	　In the current version, SWF cannot be played in layer drawing mode.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="videolayer">
	<shortinfo> Video layer settings </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="channel">
			<shortinfo> Channel </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> 1 or 2 </format>
			<info>
				　In layer drawing mode, video can be played on two channels at the same time.<BR>
				　The slot attribute is for when you want to play different videos at the same time, and the channel attribute is for when you want to play the same video on two layers (for example, the front layer and the back layer).<BR>
				　This attribute specifies for which channel to set the layer.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="page">
			<shortinfo> page </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> "fore" or "back" </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the front page ("fore") or the back page ("back").<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="layer">
			<shortinfo> layer </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Layer number (0-) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the layer number you want to display.
			</info>
		</attrib>

	</attribs>

	<remarks>
	　In layer drawing mode, specify the layer on which you want to display the video image. The layer size automatically changes to the size of the video.<BR>
	　Use <ref tag="clearvideolayer">clearvideolayer</ref> tags to remove this setting.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="clearvideolayer">
	<shortinfo> Video layer release </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
		<attrib name="channel">
			<shortinfo> Channel </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> 1 or 2 </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the channel you want to cancel drawing in layer drawing mode.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
	　Release the layer set with the <ref tag="videolayer">videolayer</ref> tag.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="videosegloop">
	<shortinfo> Video segment loop playback </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
		<attrib name="start">
			<shortinfo> Start frame number </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Frame number </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the starting point of the loop.
			</info>
		</attrib>
		<attrib name="end">
			<shortinfo> End frame number </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Frame number </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the end point of the loop.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
	　Loop playback is performed within the section indicated by the start and end attributes.<BR>
	This tag is valid only in layer drawing mode.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="cancelvideosegloop">
	<shortinfo> Cancel video segment loop playback </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
	Release the segment loop set by the <ref tag="videosegloop">videosegloop</ref> tag.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="videoevent">
	<shortinfo> Occurrence of a period event </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
		<attrib name="frame">
			<shortinfo> Frame number </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Frame number </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the frame number where the period event occurs.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
	　A period event can be generated at a specified frame.<BR>
	　Period events can be awaited with <ref tag="wp">wp</ref> tags.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="cancelvideoevent">
	<shortinfo> Cancel period event </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
	Cancel the period event set by the <ref tag="videoevent">videoevent</ref> tag.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="pausevideo">
	<shortinfo> Pause video </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
	　Pauses video playback.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="rewindvideo">
	<shortinfo> Video rewind </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
	　Rewind the video to the beginning.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="preparevideo">
	<shortinfo> Preparing for video playback </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
	Prepare the video for playback.<BR>
	Use this function to prevent undrawn images from being displayed in layer drawing mode.<BR>
	Be sure to put the [wp] tag immediately after this tag and wait for completion.<BR>
	This tag is valid only in layer drawing mode.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="resetwait">
	<shortinfo> Initialize weights </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
	<remarks>
		　Set the time origin used in mode=until of the <ref tag="wait">wait</ref> tag.<BR>
		　Do not write a label that can save a bookmark between this tag and the wait tag (since saving a bookmark on the way does not save this information).
	</remarks>
	<example>
		[resetwait]<BR>
		[wait mode=until time=3000]<BR>
		; ↑ Wait 3 seconds after resetwait
	</example>
</tag>


<tag name="wait">
	<shortinfo> Put weight </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="time">
			<shortinfo> time </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Time (ms) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the weight in milliseconds.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="mode">
			<shortinfo> Weight method </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "normal" (default) or "until" </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the weight method.<BR>
				　If you specify "normal" or omit this attribute, you will simply wait for the time specified by time.<BR>
				　If "until" is specified, the elapsed seconds from the time origin set by the <ref tag="resetwait">resetwait</ref> tag are regarded as specified by time, and the system waits until the specified time. Do not wait if the specified time has already passed.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="canskip">
			<shortinfo> Can you skip </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true (default) or false </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies whether this weight can be skipped with a mouse click or keyboard. If false is specified, the weight cannot be skipped with a mouse click or keyboard.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Put the weight.<BR>
		　You can wait from the current time (mode="normal") or wait from the time origin specified by the <ref tag="resetwait">resetwait</ref> tag (mode="until").<BR>
		　In the case of mode="until", if the specified time has already passed, the variable kag.lastWaitTime contains 0. So, if you make a judgment like [if exp="kag.lastWaitTime!=0"], you can determine whether "if the specified time has not passed yet" (in many cases, if the process has caught up).<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="waitclick">
	<shortinfo> Wait for click </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
	<remarks>
		　Wait for the click.<BR>
		　The differences from the <ref tag="l">l</ref> and <ref tag="p">p</ref> tags are that they cannot be skipped, that the click wait symbol is not displayed, that they cannot pinch / follow a bookmark while waiting, and that they cannot perform other skip operations.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>



<tag name="wc">
	<shortinfo> Insert weight for the number of characters </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="time">
			<shortinfo> word count </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> word count </format>
			<info>
				　Wait the same amount of time to display the number of characters specified here. 
				The time required for one character is specified by the <ref tag="delay">delay</ref> tag.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Insert the weight for the number of characters.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="autowc">
	<shortinfo> Automatic weight </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="enabled">
			<shortinfo>  Whether to enable auto weight </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false </format>
			<info>
				　Specify true to enable automatic weighting, false to disable it.<BR>
				　If omitted, the settings will not be changed.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="ch">
			<shortinfo> Characters for auto weight </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Target character </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the character to put auto weight. After the specified character, there is a weight for the number of characters specified by the time attribute.<BR>
				　If omitted, the settings will not be changed.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="time">
			<shortinfo> weight </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Weight (character units) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the time to put the auto weight in the number of characters.<BR>
				　For each character specified in the ch attribute, you can specify the time separated by a comma.<BR>
				　If only one time is specified, the time is set for all characters specified in the ch tag.<BR>
				　If this attribute is omitted, 4 is assumed.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　You can add a specified number of weights after a specific character.<BR>
		　After the character specified by the ch attribute is displayed, the time specified by the time attribute is entered as a weight.<BR>
		　Multiple characters can be specified with the ch tag, and correspondingly, the timing can be specified for each character with the time attribute.<BR>
	</remarks>

	<example>
		[autowc enabled=true ch="、。・" time="3,5,3"]<BR>
		; ↑ Weights for 3, 5, and 3 characters are added to each character of "、。・"
	</example>

</tag>



<tag name="wp">
	<shortinfo> Waiting for video period event </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
		<attrib name="for">
			<shortinfo> Event type </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format>  	One of "loop", "period", "prepare", "segLoop" </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies the type of event to wait.<BR>
				　If "loop" is specified, wait for the loop end.<BR>
				　Specify "period" to wait for a period event.<BR>
				　If "prepare" is specified, wait for preparevideo to be prepared.<BR>
				　If "segLoop" is specified, wait for the end of the segment loop.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		Wait for a period event.<BR>
		If the for attribute is not specified, waits for all events, and continues processing when any of them occurs.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="wt">
	<shortinfo> Wait for transition to end </shortinfo>
	<group> Layer operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="canskip">
			<shortinfo> Whether you can skip </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true (default) or false </format>
			<info>
				　If you specify true, you can skip waiting for the end of the transition by clicking.<BR>
				　If you specify false, you cannot skip.<BR>
				　However, please note that if the click skip is prohibited by the <ref tag="clickskip">clickskip</ref> tag, this skip cannot be performed.<BR>
				　If you skip waiting for the end of the transition on the way, it will immediately transition to the state after the switch.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Wait for the transition to finish.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="wm">
	<shortinfo> Waiting for automatic movement to end </shortinfo>
	<group> Layer operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="canskip">
			<shortinfo> Whether you can skip </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true (default) or false </format>
			<info>
				　If you specify true, you can skip waiting for the end of automatic movement by clicking.<BR>
				　If you specify false, you cannot skip.<BR>
				　However, please note that if the click skip is prohibited by the <ref tag="clickskip">clickskip</ref> tag, this skip cannot be performed.<BR>
				　If you skip waiting for the end of automatic movement in the middle, it will immediately move to the final position.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>
	<remarks>
		　Wait for the end of the automatic move.
	</remarks>
</tag>



<tag name="wv">
	<shortinfo> Waiting for video playback to end </shortinfo>
	<group> Sound effects / BGM / Video operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="slot">
			<shortinfo> Movie object number </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Movie object number (0~) </format>
			<info>
				Specify the movie object number that performs this operation.<BR>
				If omitted, 0 is assumed.<BR>
				When operating multiple movies at the same time, change the value of numMovies in Config.tjs to the required number.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
		<attrib name="canskip">
			<shortinfo> Can you skip </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false (default) </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies whether video playback can be skipped with a mouse click.<BR>
				　Specifying true enables video playback to be skipped with a mouse click.<BR>
				　However, please note that if the click skip is prohibited by the <ref tag="clickskip">clickskip</ref> tag, this skip cannot be performed.<BR>
				　Also, if skipped, the video will automatically stop playing.
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>


	<remarks>
		　Wait for the video to finish playing, ready to play with the <ref tag="preparevideo">preparevideo</ref> tag, or a period event with the <ref tag="videoevent">videoevent</ref> tag.<BR>
		　You cannot wait for the end of SWF (Shockwave Flash) playback. Please wait for the necessary time with <ref tag="wait">wait</ref> tags and take other measures.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="wq">
	<shortinfo> Waiting for screen shaking to end </shortinfo>
	<group> System operation </group>
 	<attribs>
		<attrib name="canskip">
			<shortinfo> Whether you can skip </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false (default) </format>
			<info>
				　If you specify true, you can skip waiting for the end of the transition by clicking.<BR>
				　If you specify false, you cannot skip.<BR>
				　However, please note that if the click skip is prohibited by the <ref tag="clickskip">clickskip</ref> tag, this skip cannot be performed.<BR>
				　If you skip waiting for the end of the transition on the way, it will immediately transition to the state after the switch.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Wait for the shaking that started with the <ref tag="quake">quake</ref> tag to end.
	</remarks>
</tag>



<tag name="current">
	<shortinfo> Specify the message layer to be operated </shortinfo>
	<group> Message operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="layer">
			<shortinfo> Layer name </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "message0" or "message1" </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the message layer to be operated.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="page">
			<shortinfo> page </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "fore" (default) or "back" </format>
			<info>
				　 Specify whether to target the layer of the front (fore) screen or the layer of the back (back) screen.If omitted, it is assumed to be a table page.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="withback">
			<shortinfo> Whether to draw on the back page </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false (default) </format>
			<info>
				　If the front page is the target, specify whether to draw characters on the back page as well. If this attribute is omitted, false is assumed.
				　You may need to draw characters on the back page at the same time, for example, if you want a transition to proceed at the same time.
			</info>
		</attrib>

	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Specify the message layer to be operated. After that, the specification of text attributes in text and <ref tag="font">font</ref> tags, the waiting for clicks on <ref tag="l">l</ref> tags, etc. are performed for this layer.<BR>
		　Note that message0 is visible by default, but message1 will not be displayed unless visible=true with <ref tag="layopt">layopt</ref> tags etc.
	</remarks>
</tag>

<tag name="er">
	<shortinfo> Erase message layer characters </shortinfo>
	<group> Message operation </group>

	<remarks>
		　Erases characters on the current operation target message layer.<BR>
		　Unlike the <ref tag="ct">ct</ref> tag, the er tag erases the characters on the current message layer and resets the character attributes and style. Does not revert to message0.
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="backlay">
	<shortinfo> Copy layer information from front page to back page </shortinfo>
	<group> Layer operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="layer">
			<shortinfo> Target layer </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "base" or an integer greater than or equal to 0 or message0 or message1 or message </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the target layer.<BR>
				　If you specify base, it will be the background layer.<BR>
				　Specifying an integer greater than or equal to 0 results in a foreground layer.<BR>
				　Specifying message0 or message1 will be the message layer. If only message is specified, the message layer of the current operation target specified by the <ref tag="current">current</ref> tag will be the target. The copy will be made).<BR>
				　If omitted, the information of all layers will be copied to the back page.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>
	</attribs>


	<remarks>
		　Copies information of the specified layer or all layers from the front page to the back page.<BR>
		　What is copied is the same information that is copied with the <ref tag="copylay">copylay</ref> tag.<BR>
		　The <ref tag="trans">trans</ref> tag replaces the image on the front page layer with the image on the back page layer. Therefore, use this method to transfer the image to the back page with this backlay tag before the transition, operate the layer on the back page, and then perform the transition.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="copylay">
	<shortinfo> Copy layer information </shortinfo>
	<group> Layer operation </group>

	<attribs>
		<attrib name="srclayer">
			<shortinfo> Copy source layer </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> "base" or 0 or 1 or 2 or message0 or message1 or message </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the layer to be copied.<BR>
				　The layer specified by this attribute and the srcpage attribute will be the copy source.<BR>
				　If you specify base, it will be the background layer.<BR>
				　Specifying 0 or 1 or 2 will result in a foreground layer.<BR>
				　Specifying message0 or message1 will be the message layer. If only message is specified, the message layer of the current operation target specified by the <ref tag="current">current</ref> tag is targeted.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="destlayer">
			<shortinfo> Copy destination layer </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> "base" or 0 or 1 or 2 or message0 or message1 or message </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the layer to copy to.<BR>
				　The copy destination is the layer specified by this attribute and the destpage attribute.<BR>
				　If you specify base, it will be the background layer.<BR>
				　Specifying 0 or 1 or 2 will result in a foreground layer.<BR>
				　Specifying message0 or message1 will be the message layer. If only message is specified, the message layer of the current operation target specified by the <ref tag="current">current</ref> tag is targeted.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="srcpage">
			<shortinfo> Copy source page </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "fore" or "back" </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the page to be copied.<BR>
				　The layer specified by this attribute and the srclayer attribute will be the copy source.<BR>
				　If "fore" is specified, the front page is specified, and if "back" is specified, the back page is specified.
				If omitted, it is assumed that "fore" is specified.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="destpage">
			<shortinfo> Destination page </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "fore" or "back" </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the copy destination page.<BR>
				　The layer specified by this attribute and the destlayer attribute becomes the copy source.<BR>
				　If "fore" is specified, the front page is specified, and if "back" is specified, the back page is specified.
				If omitted, it is assumed that "fore" is specified.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

	</attribs>


	<remarks>
		　Copies the information of the specified layer.<BR>
		　However, you can only copy layers of the same type (background layers, foreground layers, message layers).<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="pimage">
	<shortinfo> Partial image loading </shortinfo>
	<group> Layer operation </group>
	<attribs>
		<attrib name="storage">
			<shortinfo> Image file name </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Image file name </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the image to add and load.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="layer">
			<shortinfo> Target layer </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> "base" or an integer greater than or equal to 0 </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the layer to add and load the image.<BR>
				Add an image and read it. Specify a "base" to load the image into the background layer, or specify an integer greater than or equal to 0 to load the image into the corresponding foreground layer.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="page">
			<shortinfo> page </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "back" or "fore" </format>
			<info>
				　Specify whether to target the front (fore) screen or the back (back) screen.
				If omitted, it is assumed to be a table page.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="key">
			<shortinfo> Color key </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0xRRGGBB format or palette index number or "adapt" </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies which color of the image specified by storage is to be the extraction color. If omitted, the extraction color will be invalid. 
				　If you specify the extraction color in hexadecimal number in the format key=0xRRGGBB, the part painted with RR (red) GG (green) BB (blue) will be transparent as the extraction color.
				For example, key=0xff00ff specifies (r,g,b)=(255,0,255), which means that the true magenta part is to be made a transparent color and transparent.<BR>
				　If you simply specify a numerical value, the numerical value of that palette index will be the extraction color. Effective for 16-color / 256-color images.<BR>
				　If you specify key=adapt, the extraction color will be determined automatically.
				The color used is the color most used in the top line of the image.
				Effective for 16-color / 256-color images.<BR>
				　If you use a mask image, you do not need to specify this attribute.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="dx">
			<shortinfo> Image reading destination x coordinate </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Pixel unit </format>
			<info>
				Specify the leftmost x-coordinate (in coordinates of the target layer) to be overlaid or copied.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="dy">
			<shortinfo> Image reading destination y coordinate </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> Pixel unit </format>
			<info>
				Specifies the top y-coordinate (in coordinates of the target layer) to be overlaid or copied.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="sx">
			<shortinfo> Image reading source x coordinate </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Pixel unit </format>
			<info>
				Specifies the leftmost x-coordinate (in the image to be added and loaded) of the source to be overlaid or copied.<BR>
				　If omitted, it is assumed to be 0.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="sy">
			<shortinfo> Image reading source y coordinate </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Pixel unit </format>
			<info>
				Specifies the top y-coordinate (in the image to be additionally loaded) of the top to be overlaid or copied.<BR>
				　If omitted, it is assumed to be 0.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="sw">
			<shortinfo> Image reading source width </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Pixel unit </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the width to overlap or copy.<BR>
				　If omitted, it is assumed to be the full width of the image to be loaded.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="sh">
			<shortinfo> Image reading source height </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Pixel unit </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the height to overlap or copy.<BR>
				　If omitted, it is assumed to be the full height of the image to be loaded.
			</info>
		</attrib>


		<attrib name="mode">
			<shortinfo> Overlay mode </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "copy" or "opaque" or "pile" (default) or "alpha" or "add" or "sub" or "mul" or "dodge" or "darken" or "lighten" or "screen" or "psadd" Or "pssub" or "psmul" or "psscreen" or "psoverlay" or "pshlight" or "psslight" or "psdodge" or "psdodge5" or "psburn" or "pslighten" or "psdarken" or "psdiff" or "psdiff5" or "psexcl" </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies whether to superimpose, simply copy, or perform the operation on the rectangular area specified by each attribute of sx sy sw sh.<BR>
				　If "copy" or "opaque" is specified, the rectangular area will be copied. "copy" and "opaque" have the same meaning.<BR>
				　If "pile" or "alpha" is specified, superposition using alpha synthesis is performed. "pile" and "alpha" have the same meaning.<BR>
				　When "addalpha" is specified, superposition by additive alpha synthesis is performed.<BR>
				　For other modes, see the mode attribute of the <ref tag="image">image</ref> tag.<BR>
				　If omitted, "pile" is assumed. Exceptionally, TLG5 / 6 images have information on which overlay mode is superimposed on the image (this information is the same as that read by the <ref tag="image">image</ref> tag). In this case, if this attribute is omitted, the superimposition mode that the image has as information is used.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="opacity">
			<shortinfo> Opacity </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Opacity (0 (completely transparent) to 255 (completely opaque)) </format>
			<info>
				　The opacity of the overlay when "pile" is specified in the mode attribute, or the intensity of the operation when any of "add" "sub" "mul" "dodge" "darken" "lighten" "screen" is specified Is specified.<BR>
				　If omitted, 255 is assumed.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Adds an image to the specified layer and loads it.<BR>
		　You can overlay or copy a part of another image file to a specified part of a specified layer.<BR>
		　You can add and load any number of images. However, please note that no matter how much, if you add and load an image, the information that "the image was added and loaded" will be accumulated more and more.<BR>
		　If you load an image into a layer with a new <ref tag="image">image</ref> tag or release an image with a <ref tag="freeimage">freeimage</ref> tag, the added images and their information will be lost.<BR>
		　For example, if you want to add an image to a layer at regular intervals and load and animate it, you may want to use the animation function instead of this tag.<BR>
		　This tag is used to load an image with the image tag, but to change only a part of the image and write it immediately after the corresponding image tag.
	</remarks>
</tag>


<tag name="ptext">
	<shortinfo> Drawing characters on layers </shortinfo>
	<group> Layer operation </group>
	<attribs>

		<attrib name="layer">
			<shortinfo> Target layer </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> "base" or an integer greater than or equal to 0 </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the layer to draw characters.<BR>
				If "base" is specified, characters are drawn on the background layer, and if an integer greater than 0 is specified, characters are drawn on the corresponding foreground layer.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="page">
			<shortinfo> page </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> "back" or "fore" </format>
			<info>
				　Specify whether to target the front (fore) screen or the back (back) screen.
				If omitted, it is assumed to be a table page.
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="x">
			<shortinfo> x coordinate value </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> pixel unit </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the horizontal position to draw characters in pixel units.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="y">
			<shortinfo> y coordinate value </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> pixel unit </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the vertical position to draw characters in pixel units.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="text">
			<shortinfo> The character to draw </shortinfo>
			<required> yes </required>
			<format> String </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the character string to be drawn.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="vertical">
			<shortinfo> Whether vertical writing </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> false (default) or true </format>
			<info>
				　Specify whether to write vertically. If you specify true, it will be vertical writing.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="angle">
			<shortinfo> Character drawing angle </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 10 times the angle </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the angle of text drawing. Specify a value 10 times the angle (0 to 3600).<BR>
				　If omitted, 0 is assumed for horizontal writing, and 2700 is specified for vertical writing.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="size">
			<shortinfo> font size </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Character size (pixel unit) </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the font size in pixel units.<BR>
				　If you omit this attribute, 12 is selected.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="face">
			<shortinfo> Font name </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> Font name </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the font name.<BR>
				　Font names cannot be ambiguous. Please specify space, half-width / full-width exactly.<BR>
				　You can specify multiple font names separated by commas. In this case, if there is a font written at the beginning, it will be selected with priority.<BR>
				　Example: face="Noto Sans,Arial"<BR>
				　The font for vertical writing is automatically set, so there is no need to put the @ mark at the beginning of the font name.<BR>
				　If this attribute is omitted, MS PGothic is selected.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="color">
			<shortinfo> Letter color </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0xRRGGBB format </format>
			<info>
				　Specify the font color in 0xRRGGBB format.<BR>
				　If omitted, it is assumed to be 0x000000.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="italic">
			<shortinfo> Whether italic </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false (default) </format>
			<info>
				　Specifies whether characters are italic. Specify true to make italic.<BR>
				　If this attribute is omitted, it is assumed to be false.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="shadow">
			<shortinfo> Whether to show shadows </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true (default) or false </format>
			<info>
			　Specify whether to add shadow to characters. If true is specified, the shadow will be cast.<BR>
			　You cannot specify true for both edge and shadow.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="edge">
			<shortinfo> Whether to use border characters </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false (default) </format>
			<info>
			　Specify whether to use a blank character (border character). If true is specified, it becomes a bag character.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="edgecolor">
			<shortinfo> Bag character bag color </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0xRRGGBB format </format>
			<info>
			　Specifies the color of the text bag in the format 0xRRGGBB.<BR>
			　If omitted, it is assumed that 0x000000 is specified.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="shadowcolor">
			<shortinfo> Shadow color </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> 0xRRGGBB format </format>
			<info>
			　Specifies the color of the shadow in 0xRRGGBB format.<BR>
			　If omitted, it is assumed that 0x000000 is specified.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

		<attrib name="bold">
			<shortinfo> Bold </shortinfo>
			<required> no </required>
			<format> true or false (default) </format>
			<info>
			　Specify whether to make the characters bold. If true is specified, bold characters will be used.<BR>
			</info>
		</attrib>

	</attribs>

	<remarks>
		　Draw characters on the specified layer.<BR>
		　Unlike displaying it in the message layer, the content drawn with this tag is recorded in the bookmark (it is reproduced even if you read the bookmark).<BR>
		　Text is erased when you load an image into the layer.<BR>
		　This is useful when you want to keep displaying some numerical status on the screen.<BR>
	</remarks>
</tag>


